This is a great recipe. I use pearl couscous, instead of cooking in water I use the method in this recipe to cook the cousous: http://www.wholefoodsmarket.com/recipes/2024 Heat 1 tablespoon of the olive oil in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Add couscous and cook, stirring frequently, until toasted, about 5 minutes. Stir in water and salt and bring to a simmer. Cover and simmer until water is absorbed and couscous is just tender, 10 to 12 minutes. Ratio couscous to water: 1 1/3 cups couscous to 1 3/4 cups water. I may use a bit more garlic paste, and I always use french lentils as they hold their shape very well. Gorgeous looking and wonderful tasting salad.

